        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 10:51PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1050 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms between Chilhowie and Richlands, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Excessive rainfall may flood roadside
ditches causing debris to be washed onto the highway.
Flooding of poor drainage areas also possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Saltville...
Chilhowie...
Cedar Bluff...
and Mount Rogers National Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
